  "text": "Owing to the weighted Poincaré inequality of Corollary 4.3, we can adapt the proof of [CITATION_1] Lemma 2.3 ] to obtain interpolation estimates in the weighted L 2 -norm. These estimates allow a disparate mesh size on the extended direction, relative to the coordinate directions x i , i = 1, . . . , n, which may in turn be graded. This is the principal difference with [CITATION_2] Lemma 2.3] where, however, the domain must be a cube. 18) and, for all v ∈ H 2 (ω v , y α ) and j = 1, . . . , n + 1, we have",
